    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/03-pretraining/02-data-cleaning-dedup.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Raw crawl -> clean corpus is a cascade funnel: each stage strips a characteristic kind of junk (foreign-language, boilerplate/spam, exact mirror copies, near-duplicates, benchmark leakage) and only ~30% of raw tokens survive as high-signal training data.; MinHash: the minimum hash value over a set is equally likely to land on any element of the union, so two documents share a MinHash entry with probability EXACTLY equal to their Jaccard similarity |A intersect B| / |A union B| -- that is why a fraction of matching signature entries is an unbiased Jaccard estimator.; LSH banding turns the smooth MinHash estimator into a sharp yes/no threshold: split the k-row signature into b bands of r rows, call two docs candidates if ANY band matches exactly, and the resulting probability 1-(1-s^r)^b is an S-curve whose knee sits near (1/b)^(1/r) -- (b,r) is the knob trading recall against verification cost.; Exact dedup catches only byte-identical (normalized) copies; fuzzy dedup is needed for the far larger pool of near-duplicates (re-rendered HTML, mirror sites, shared boilerplate).\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  dedup-paragraph-minhash-pipeline\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
